r Lucy Shi of UIC" size="thumbnail" return="" srcset="https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Lucy-Shi-of-UIC-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Lucy-Shi-of-UIC-500x500.jpg 500w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Lucy-Shi-of-UIC-600x600.jpg 600w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Lucy-Shi-of-UIC-414x414.jpg 414w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Lucy-Shi-of-UIC-55x55.jpg 55w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Lucy-Shi-of-UIC-80x80.jpg 80w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Lucy-Shi-of-UIC-130x130.jpg 130w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Lucy-Shi-of-UIC-100x100.jpg 100w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Lucy-Shi-of-UIC-435x435.jpg 435w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px" /></a></div><article class="news-article wrapper"> <span class="news-title"><a class="post_title w4pl_post_title" href="https://www.ece.uic.edu/2018/08/01/researchers-put-a-new-spin-on-cooling-electronic-hotspots/" title="View Researchers Put a New Spin on Cooling Electronic Hotspots">Researchers Put a New Spin on Cooling Electronic Hotspots</a></span> <span class="post-date">August 1, 2018</span><div class="post-excerpt">The longevity of electronic devices is tested in many ways as they endure the rigors of daily usage. Even when they are treated with the utmost care, they still have a major challenge to overcome – the removal of heat. To alleviate this problem, ECE Assistant Professor Junxia “Lucy” Shi and her team of researchers in the Advanced Semiconductor Materials and Devices Laboratory at UIC are focusing on using a novel method for cooling hotspots in electronics and capturing the wasted heat to use to power the devices. The new technique additionally has the potential to expand the longevity of electronic components. The results of their research were recently published in the prestigious journals Scientific Reports and Physical Review Materials.&hellip;</div> <a class="read_more" href="https://www.ece.uic.edu/2018/08/01/researchers-put-a-new-spin-on-cooling-electronic-hotspots/" title="More... Researchers Put a New Spin on Cooling Electronic Hotspots">More...</a></article></div></div><div class="masonry-item"><div class="inner content-wrap k2t-element-hover"><div class="post-img attachment-thumb_150x150 size-thumb_150x150 wp-post-image"> <a href="https://www.ece.uic.edu/2018/07/17/ece-international-program-sets-the-stage-for-student-success/"><img width="150" height="150" src="https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/ECE-Alex_Italian-ProgramWEB-150x150.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail" alt="ECE Alex_Italian Program" size="thumbnail" return="" srcset="https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/ECE-Alex_Italian-ProgramWEB-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/ECE-Alex_Italian-ProgramWEB-500x500.jpg 500w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/ECE-Alex_Italian-ProgramWEB-414x414.jpg 414w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/ECE-Alex_Italian-ProgramWEB-55x55.jpg 55w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/ECE-Alex_Italian-ProgramWEB-80x80.jpg 80w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/ECE-Alex_Italian-ProgramWEB-130x130.jpg 130w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/ECE-Alex_Italian-ProgramWEB-100x100.jpg 100w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/ECE-Alex_Italian-ProgramWEB-435x435.jpg 435w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px" /></a></div><article class="news-article wrapper"> <span class="news-title"><a class="post_title w4pl_post_title" href="https://www.ece.uic.edu/2018/07/17/ece-international-program-sets-the-stage-for-student-success/" title="View ECE International Program Sets the Stage for Student Success">ECE International Program Sets the Stage for Student Success</a></span> <span class="post-date">July 17, 2018</span><div class="post-excerpt">Located in the heart of Chicago, UIC offers students a unique educational experience and work opportunities in a world-class city. For Alex Iacobucci, UIC’s Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering (ECE) set the stage for his professional career as an engineer and provides him with the opportunity to do some acting outside the office. Iacobucci, came to ECE through the UIC College of Engineering, which has a partnership with one of the top engineering schools in Italy – Polytechnic University of Turin – and provides the students with a dual master’s degree. At the completion of the program, students get a degree from the Italian university and UIC. They take one semester in Italy and one semester at UIC, where&hellip;</div> <a class="read_more" href="https://www.ece.uic.edu/2018/07/17/ece-international-program-sets-the-stage-for-student-success/" title="More... ECE International Program Sets the Stage for Student Success">More...</a></article></div></div><div class="masonry-item"><div class="inner content-wrap k2t-element-hover"><div class="post-img attachment-thumb_150x150 size-thumb_150x150 wp-post-image"> <a href="https://www.ece.uic.edu/2018/06/25/celebrating-the-life-of-professor-emeritus-wolfgang-martin-boerner/"><img width="150" height="150" src="https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Prof-BoernerWEB-150x150.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail" alt="Professor Wolgang Boerner" size="thumbnail" return="" srcset="https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Prof-BoernerWEB-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Prof-BoernerWEB-55x55.jpg 55w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Prof-BoernerWEB-80x80.jpg 80w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Prof-BoernerWEB-130x130.jpg 130w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Prof-BoernerWEB-100x100.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px" /></a></div><article class="news-article wrapper"> <span class="news-title"><a class="post_title w4pl_post_title" href="https://www.ece.uic.edu/2018/06/25/celebrating-the-life-of-professor-emeritus-wolfgang-martin-boerner/" title="View Celebrating the Life of Professor Emeritus Wolfgang-Martin Boerner">Celebrating the Life of Professor Emeritus Wolfgang-Martin Boerner</a></span> <span class="post-date">June 25, 2018</span><div class="post-excerpt">In Memoriam: Professor Emeritus Wolfgang-Martin Boerner July 26, 1937- May 25, 2018It is with the greatest sadness and regret that we announce that our dear friend and highly admired colleague Electrical and Computer Engineering (ECE) Professor Emeritus Wolfgang-Martin Boerner passed away on May 25, 2018 at the age of 80.He had an illustrious career and was undoubtedly a most eminent researcher and giant in the general area of electromagnetics and especially in remote sensing and polarimetric imaging radar. Boerner had a distinguished record of accomplishments and recognition, and was a Life Fellow of IEEE, Optical Society of America, International Society for Optical and Photogrammetric Engineering, Society for Exploration Geophysics, SPIE, American Association for the Advancement of Science, and Institute of&hellip;</div> <a class="read_more" href="https://www.ece.uic.edu/2018/06/25/celebrating-the-life-of-professor-emeritus-wolfgang-martin-boerner/" title="More... Celebrating the Life of Professor Emeritus Wolfgang-Martin Boerner">More...</a></article></div></div><div class="masonry-item"><div class="inner content-wrap k2t-element-hover"><div class="post-img attachment-thumb_150x150 size-thumb_150x150 wp-post-image"> <a href="https://www.ece.uic.edu/2018/06/01/ece-students-show-talent-and-ingenuity-at-design-expo/"><img width="150" height="150" src="https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/ECE_Expo-2018-150x150.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail" alt="ECE Senior Design Expo at UIC in Chicago" size="thumbnail" return="" srcset="https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/ECE_Expo-2018-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/ECE_Expo-2018-55x55.jpg 55w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/ECE_Expo-2018-80x80.jpg 80w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/ECE_Expo-2018-130x130.jpg 130w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/ECE_Expo-2018-100x100.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px" /></a></div><article class="news-article wrapper"> <span class="news-title"><a class="post_title w4pl_post_title" href="https://www.ece.uic.edu/2018/06/01/ece-students-show-talent-and-ingenuity-at-design-expo/" title="View ECE Students Show Talent and Ingenuity at Design Expo">ECE Students Show Talent and Ingenuity at Design Expo</a></span> <span class="post-date">June 1, 2018</span><div class="post-excerpt">ECE students showed their talents and ingenuity during the 29th Annual UIC Engineering Senior Design Expo on Friday, April 27, at the UIC Forum. ECE students were among more than 528 seniors from the College of Engineering (COE) presenting within 27 project categories. Eleven ECE teams were named Best in Category – some teams tied for first - in the eight categories in which they participated. The Best in Category In the Electronics Engineering category, Paul Benjamin Johnson and Joshua H. Tang nabbed the top spot with their Velo Nexus.The project leverages the power of a smartphone to add additional sensors easily and on demand allow for variability for an individual user’s needs and wants related to a bicycle ride.  Controlling&hellip;</div> <a class="read_more" href="https://www.ece.uic.edu/2018/06/01/ece-students-show-talent-and-ingenuity-at-design-expo/" title="More... ECE Students Show Talent and Ingenuity at Design Expo">More...</a></article></div></div><div class="masonry-item"><div class="inner content-wrap k2t-element-hover"><div class="post-img attachment-thumb_150x150 size-thumb_150x150 wp-post-image"> <a href="https://www.ece.uic.edu/2018/05/18/alumnus-on-the-road-to-success-with-tech-startup/"><img width="150" height="150" src="https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Suyu-Zhang-of-ChowbusWEB-150x150.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail" alt="ECE Alum Suyu Zhang of Chicago tech startup Chowbus" size="thumbnail" return="" srcset="https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Suyu-Zhang-of-ChowbusWEB-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Suyu-Zhang-of-ChowbusWEB-55x55.jpg 55w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Suyu-Zhang-of-ChowbusWEB-80x80.jpg 80w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Suyu-Zhang-of-ChowbusWEB-130x130.jpg 130w, https://www.ece.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Suyu-Zhang-of-ChowbusWEB-100x100.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px" /></a></div><article class="news-article wrapper"> <span class="news-title"><a class="post_title w4pl_post_title" href="https://www.ece.uic.edu/2018/05/18/alumnus-on-the-road-to-success-with-tech-startup/" title="View Alumnus on the Road to Success with Tech Startup">Alumnus on the Road to Success with Tech Startup</a></span> <span class="post-date">May 18, 2018</span><div class="post-excerpt">Ordering food online can get expensive quickly when you add the delivery fee and tip to the total. Unless the order is placed through the online app Chowbus, a Chicago-based tech startup that charges a modest $1 for deliveries.Co-founded by UIC alumnus Suyu Zhang, who serves as the company’s chief technology officer, Chowbus curates and delivers top-notch ethnic food with a rotating menu. The company started selling food online in 2015. Zhang has a background in mobile apps and he and the co-founder started working on their app, which was launched in March of 2016. Now, they are generating approximately $600,000 a month. The idea for a low delivery fee came from personal experiences ordering food while Zhang was working&hellip;</div> <a class="read_more" href="https://www.ece.uic.edu/2018/05/18/alumnus-on-the-road-to-success-with-tech-startup/" title="More... Alumnus on the Road to Success with Tech Startup">More...</a></article></div></div></div></div></div></div></div> <script id="w4pl-js-984" type="text/javascript">var shorten_excerpt = function() {

var excerpts = document.getElementsByClassName('post-excerpt');
if ( document.documentElement.clientWidth > 950 || document.documentElement.clientWidth < 750) {
	var max_chars = 100;
} else {
var max_chars = 200;
}

	for (var i = 0; i < excerpts.length; ++i) {
		var excerpt = excerpts[i];
		var excerpt_string = excerpt.innerHTML;
		var words = excerpt_string.split(' ');
		var num_words = words.length;
		word_lens = [];

		for (var j = 0; j < words.length; ++j) {
			word_lens.push(words[j].length);
		}

		var display_amount = 0;
		var total = 0;
		var index = 0;
		while (total < max_chars) {
			display_amount++;
			total += word_lens[index];
			index++;
		}

		words = words.slice(0, display_amount);
		new_excerpt = words.join(' ');

		if (display_amount < num_words) {
			new_excerpt = new_excerpt + '...';
		}
		excerpt.innerHTML = new_excerpt;
	}

	return;
}


window.onload = function() {
	var titles = document.getElementsByClassName('post_title');
if ( document.documentElement.clientWidth > 950) {
	var max_chars = 60;
} else {
var max_chars = 100;
}

	for (var i = 0; i < titles.length; ++i) {
		var title = titles[i];
		var title_string = title.innerHTML;
		var words = title_string.split(' ');
		var num_words = words.length;
		word_lens = [];

		for (var j = 0; j < words.length; ++j) {
			word_lens.push(words[j].length);
		}

		var display_amount = 0;
		var total = 0;
		var index = 0;
		while (total < max_chars) {
			display_amount++;
			total += word_lens[index];
			index++;
		}

		words = words.slice(0, display_amount);
		new_title = words.join(' ');

		if (display_amount < num_words) {
			new_title = new_title + '...';
		}
		title.innerHTML = new_title;
	}

        shorten_excerpt();
	return;
}



